pecially when in groups or raids.<br>
<br>
The designers introduced “Bane” spells a while back ago, but these spell are only available for level 60 wizards. However wizards need something that would make them desirable at low and mid levels as well. The games designers should consider giving wizards “Bane” spells for more creature types - and more importantly lower levels.<br>
<br>
Ideally these spells should require some research and questing. Additionally they should require a special researched regent to cast. These new “Bane” spell types could include orc, goblin, gnoll, froglok, etc. Increasing the damage output in this fashion will not disrupt the game balance and more importantly help make wizards become more appealing to groups. A wizard can now either choose to spend time researching, gathering items and material used to create these powerful spells or simply use what they have available currently. The following is an example: <br>
<br>
Gnoll Bane {the designers will think of nicer names}<br>
Level: 16, INT: 135 <br>
Costs: Mana: 160, Stamina: 60 + (1 per level)<br>
Evocation – Research and Quest Only<br>
Fire Based DD - 50 + (14 per Level)  +  *Special Damage<br>
Cast Time 8, Recast Time 4<br>
Regents:  Special Researched Regent<br>
Affect: Irresistible – Spell can only be used against Gnolls. *Due to the nature of these spells there is a chance of additional “Critical Damage” (much like a warrior proc).<br>
Researched Regents:  (Example - Combine: Gnoll fur, Gnoll Blood and Enchanted Clay  (yields 4 Gnoll Bane Regents))<br>
<br>
Positives:<br>
1. Increased damage to a specified mob type.<br>
2. Wizards very appealing to groups and lower level raids.<br>
3. Critical Spell damage “proc”.<br>
<br>
Negatives:<br>
1. The requirements to cast these spell are stiffer then regular spells. <br>
2. These spell have increased aggravation.<br>
3. These spells require the completion of a challenging quest and research skill.<br>
4. The spells are no-drop and can only be scribe by the wizard that fulfills the quest.<br>
5. Due to the long casting time – these spells would be hard to use outside of groups.<br>
<br>
